title: Average Weekly Earnings, Skilled and Semi-Skilled Shop Employees of First Class Railroads for United States
notes:
For Method Of Computation See Description Of The Series. Data For July 1930-1932 Were Computed By The Same Method By NBER. In February 1932 There Was A 10% Pay Cut. For Other Pay Cuts Before And After See The Source, Pp. 5-26. Source: Computed By National Industrial Conference Board From Data In "Wage Statistics", Interstate Commerce Commission.

This NBER data series q08043 appears on the NBER website in Chapter 8 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter08.html.
